ose. Also, renaming it to something like \\\"reflects...\\\" could be more honest, as the current name implies fallback when it's unsupported. Adjusting to keep things truthful sounds like the right direction!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating security manager implementation**\\n\\nI'm assessing the current tests to see if we can enhance coverage by denying RuntimePermission, which may boost compatibility with certain runtimes supporting SecurityManager (SM). I think we should implement this. Adding a boolean to check if the security manager is installed sounds prudent; we can’t overlook this. I'm considering if the current test sets throw an unchecked exception or if private methods can still be accessed. Also, I’ll ensure to check the import statements to robustly manage permissions.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Implementing security measures**\\n\\nI'm considering the need for `NativeJavaClass` when the SecurityManager (SM) is installed. If I deny access to declared members, using `Class.getDeclaredMethods` could throw a SecurityException. I’ll set up fallback calls to `getMethods`. For fields, I think I should also use `getAccessibleFields`, which can include private fields, but it might throw an exception as well. Constructors using `getDeclaredConstructors` may experience similar issues. It's clear I need to implement denying RuntimePermission for added security!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_KNGAlnFi2ltOb0QZOQ8ob9Po|fc_0f7eb2e5bab4dc30016a27467c0dcc8190a68df23ea0e29188", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/JavaMembersTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"removal\")\n    void enhancedJavaAccessFallsBackToPublicMethodsWhenPrivateAccessIsDenied() {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"removal\")\n    void enhancedJavaAccessUsesPublicMembersWhenDeclaredAccessIsDenied() {\n"}, {"oldText": "        System.setSecurityManager(new ReflectAccessDenyingSecurityManager());\n", "newText": "        System.setSecurityManager(new DeclaredAccessDenyingSecurityManager());\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class ReflectAccessDenyingSecurityManager extends SecurityManager {\n", "newText": "    private static final class DeclaredAccessDenyingSecurityManager extends SecurityManager {\n"}, {"oldText": "            denyReflectAccess(permission);\n", "newText": "            denyDeclaredAccess(permission);\n"}, {"oldText": "            denyReflectAccess(permission);\n", "newText": "            denyDeclaredAccess(permission);\n"}, {"oldText": "        private void denyReflectAccess(Permission permission) {\n            if (permission instanceof ReflectPermission\n                    && \"suppressAccessChecks\".equals(permission.getName())) {\n                throw new SecurityException(permission.getName());\n            }\n        }\n", "newText": "        private void denyDeclaredAccess(Permission permission) {\n            if (permission instanceof ReflectPermission\n                    && \"suppressAccessChecks\".equals(permission.getName())) {\n                throw new SecurityException(permission.getName());\n            }\n            if (permission instanceof RuntimePermission\n                    && \"accessDeclaredMembers\".equals(permission.getName())) {\n                throw new SecurityException(permission.getName());\n            }\n        }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3791, "output": 1720, "cacheRead": 55808, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 61319, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780958809814, "responseId": "resp_0f7eb2e5bab4dc30016a27465ac1c48190bafd5fb8a5fd04d1"}}
